          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 3:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Both the Protagonist and Love Interest are forced to decide if they will stick to their external goals and succumb to their false beliefs... or work through their inner conflicts and sacrifice for love. By section's end, they work to fix their internal and external conflicts, leading to a reconciliation that reaffirms the primal importance of the relationship. The central question of will they end up together is answered, usually with a happy ending that implies marriage or a serious commitment, often at the cost of some personal sacrifice to the Protagonist. Hence the term Joyful Defeat. Both must admit defeat and embrace change to save the relationship."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "What brought the Protagonist and Love Interest back from the brink? Perhaps they realized it was a misunderstanding, there was an ex manipulating the situation, or they came to realize the relationship was more important than any external goal."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "One or both of the characters apologize to each other, and they make amends – be sure to keep this scene in line with their characters and arcs."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Resolve the internal and external conflicts while showing how the Protagonist and Love Interest have transformed so that the relationship may work."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Give the reader and the characters a moment of happily ever after."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 3 makes up the final 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Joyful Defeat occurs around the 88% mark."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Resolution occurs around the 98% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
