      {
        "beatId": 2,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Act 3:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "This section introduces the \"all is lost\" moment where everything seems to fall apart. The consequences of the swivel decision yield disaster as private motivations are revealed, seeming betrayals are uncovered, and either the relationship and/or the Protagonist’s goal is seemingly lost forever. This is when previous false beliefs and doubts come back to the surface, and the relationship falls apart, leading to a breakup and doubt as to whether they will ever be able to find their way back to each other."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "What event or betrayal triggers the Protagonist's fears about their relationship, forcing them back into their false beliefs and doubts? For example, this could be the return of an ex, the resurfacing of a previous belief of the Love Interest, or an unexpected opportunity to achieve their external goal."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Consider deepening the tension by having more than the relationship end (e.g. the Protagonist may also lose friends, the support of family, or even their job as they cope with this new stress)."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Offer the reader an opportunity to see how the characters have returned to their old lives in an unsatisfactory way, so that everything is as it was, but a little darker and with less enjoyment. Did they make a mistake?"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 3 makes up the final 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Dark Moment/Crisis occurs around the 75% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
