            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A new development raises the stakes and clearly defines the Protagonist’s external goal. This works best when it sets the Protagonist and Love Interest at cross-purposes and/or their internal needs at odds with their external goal. One or both characters begin to see each other in a different light, raising the romantic tension. More sparks are beginning to fly, but in a state of denial, and conflict is on the horizon."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Consider how the characters' internal needs and external goals conflict with each other (e.g. the Protagonist owns a struggling café, and the Love Interest is opening a fancy new café down the street)."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Remember: Internal needs could include love, patience, humility, or courage, while external goals could include a job promotion, saving their bookstore, taking a trip, moving to a new city, etc."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Turning Point occurs around the 25% mark as we begin Act 2."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
